# Dependency Injection

## Composition Root

**Only** these locations may instantiate concrete infrastructure classes:

- `src/sentinel_anpr/bootstrap/`
- `src/sentinel_anpr/interfaces/dependency_injection/`

All other modules receive dependencies via constructor injection or framework `Depends()` resolved from the container.

## Wiring Rules

| Module | Receives | Via |
|--------|----------|-----|
| Use case | Outbound port implementations | Constructor `__init__(self, repo: SightingRepositoryPort)` |
| HTTP handler | Use case / inbound port | DI provider |
| Repository | DB session, config | Constructor (infra only) |
| ML adapter | Model path, thresholds | `ConfigurationPort` |

## Provider Layout

```
interfaces/dependency_injection/
├── containers/     # App container definition
├── providers/      # Factory functions per port
└── wiring/         # Bind interface → implementation
```

## Rules

- Handlers must not call `YoloPlateDetector()` or `Session()` directly — inject ports.
- Use cases must not import from `infrastructure/` — only port protocols.
- Prefer constructor injection over service locators and global singletons.
- One provider module per outbound port family (e.g. `persistence_providers.py`).

## Testing

- Unit-test use cases with **fake port implementations** from `tests/fixtures/fakes/`.
- Integration tests swap real adapters via test container overrides.
- Never patch concrete classes inside domain tests.

## Framework DI (when implemented)

Record framework choice in `docs/adr/`. FastAPI `Depends()` is allowed **only** in `interfaces/` — wired to application abstractions.
